  "prompt": "What are the best coffee shops with Wi-Fi in San Francisco for evening work?",
  "response": "San Francisco offers several great coffee shops with Wi-Fi that are conducive for evening work. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Flywheel Coffee Roasters**: Located near Golden Gate Park, this spot is known for its strong coffee and spacious seating, making it ideal for working into the evening.\n\n2. **Ritual Coffee Roasters**: Found in the Mission District, this shop has a vibrant atmosphere with plenty of seating and reliable Wi-Fi.\n\n3. **The Mill**: Located on Divisadero Street, The Mill offers a cozy ambiance, delicious coffee, and baked goods. It\u2019s a nice place to work later into the day.\n\n4. **Saint Frank Coffee**: Situated on Polk Street, it\u2019s known for high-quality coffee and a friendly environment, perfect for getting work done.\n\n5. **Sightglass Coffee**: On 7th Street, this spacious caf\u00e9 has a minimalist design and a strong Wi-Fi connection, great for evening productivity.\n\n6. **Atlas Cafe**: In the Mission District, Atlas Cafe offers both indoor and outdoor seating with a laid-back vibe that\u2019s great for working late.\n\nRemember that operating hours can vary, so it\u2019s a good idea to check if these places are open late into the evening before planning your visit.",
